

# ⚙ How It Works

### Step 1

IR sensor monitors object movement.

### Step 2

MQ135 continuously measures air quality.

### Step 3

ESP32 Sender collects sensor readings.

### Step 4

Data is transmitted wirelessly using ESP-NOW.

### Step 5

Receiver processes incoming packets.

### Step 6

OLED updates live monitoring data.

### Step 7

Alarm activates if intrusion is detected.

## ⚙ Working Principle

1. IR sensor continuously monitors object presence.
2. MQ135 measures surrounding air quality.
3. ESP32 sender collects sensor data.
4. Data is transmitted using ESP-NOW.
5. Receiver ESP32 receives packets.
6. OLED updates live information.
7. Speaker alarm activates on intrusion.

